Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:35.33,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,One and a half of those hours \N is a non-stop ride to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.33,0:08:39.67,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Aww, we got on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.67,0:08:41.25,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Quit complaining. {"bellyaching" too much? -QC A}{Too much I think -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:45.34,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Hey, there's a gap \N between the floor and the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.34,0:08:47.63,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,What's on the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.01,0:08:50.63,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Isn't that the driver's compartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:56.18,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,There's no way seven people're \N all crammed up in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:08:59.23,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,You never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.23,0:09:02.19,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Use your Beach Boy to attack the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.11,0:09:07.90,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.49,0:09:13.41,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Beach Boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:22.50,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,I knew there wasn't seven guys in there... {There aren't seven guys in there...} {missed a やっぱり, edited to better fit Pesci maybe -QC A}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.71,0:09:25.13,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,There's two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.55,0:09:27.21,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Got 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:34.30,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Shit. It really {\i1}is{\i0} cramped in here. {たしかに is a pretty explicit emphasis word, so added emphasis to 'is' -QC A}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:36.14,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Looks like it's just the driver in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.14,0:09:39.60,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,But they're definitely \N somewhere else on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:42.73,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Huh? Hey, wait a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:44.69,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,There's only one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:48.40,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Pretty sure I felt \N {\i1}two{\i0} living things in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.07,0:09:51.40,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,I could've sworn there was one more...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:52.45,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Hey, Pesci!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.45,0:09:56.08,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,We've gotta be real thorough here. \N We'll search this train front to back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.08,0:09:59.20,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,We'll drag Buccellati and his crew out \N no matter where they're hiding!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:00.79,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,But you stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.79,0:10:01.46,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:07.00,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,If they figure out we're here, \N they may try to stop the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:08.50,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Gotcha, Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:11.01,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,They have the girl with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:16.55,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,It won't be easy for them to\N move around or jump off the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:19.06,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,That's our big advantage here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.06,0:10:23.73,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,We'll {kill}massacre them and take the girl\N long before the train reaches Rome! {Just like ぶっ殺して, 皆殺しにして warrants a much stronger expression than just "kill". -QC A}{Rearranged the sentence a bit because idk the "We do the thing before we get to the place and then we do the thing" wording kinda made it sound like the two things they were doing are disconnected idk might just be my brain being weird though. -TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.32,0:10:30.11,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The key wasn't meant for a keyhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.11,0:10:34.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It was meant to be placed in this tortoise's shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.57,0:10:38.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Somehow, that activated its ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:44.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...and turned the key itself into \N an entrance to this place where we can hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.58,0:10:47.46,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Th-The tortoise is a Stand user?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:52.09,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,O-Ouch! {jesus FUCK}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.09,0:10:53.30,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:55.84,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm under the seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:10:58.10,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:01.52,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,B-But seriously, this is sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:03.81,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,The tortoise is like\N some kind of spaceship! {wat -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:07.73,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,But this room isn't an illusion \N or anything like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:10.48,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,It's a real, physical place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:12.61,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Even the sofa and\N other furniture are real.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.74,0:11:14.70,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The fridge has even got chilled drinks. {Budwaicer, Spalite...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:18.41,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I suppose the boss was considerate \N and left them there for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:23.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Tortoises are quiet and like being in the shade, \N and they don't move around very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.70,0:11:27.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It should help us reach Venice \N by train without worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:33.55,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Guess it doesn't make sense \N for someone to be in the locker... {Pesci's a filthy part skipper, he doesn't even KNOW about Devo the Cursed fitting in a fridge about that size -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.55,0:11:36.80,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,I really don't got my bro's instincts...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.65,0:11:48.90,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,B-Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.90,0:11:50.81,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me he...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:55.11,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,The Grateful Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.28,0:11:58.20,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,A-Are you really gonna do it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.20,0:12:00.70,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,You're gonna doom all the passengers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.70,0:12:04.12,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,We don't even know \N if they're on this train!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.12,0:12:08.62,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,I told you we had to be thorough here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:10.92,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,They're definitely here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:13.59,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,What's the big deal, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:17.76,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,Train accidents happen \N every year all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.09,0:12:20.47,Main,Prosciutto,0,0,0,,This will be less brutal.
Comment: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:27.06,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.58,0:12:52.38,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's probably just 'cause\N the room's inside of a tortoise,{"We're in a room inside a tortoise" felt needlessly clunky to me. Also, split for better balance. It does ever-so-slightly push the CPS, but I think it's within acceptable bounds. -TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:54.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,but it feels kinda muggy in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:57.34,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Narancia, you want a drink, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.97,0:13:03.93,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's all cold drinks, but we have cola,\N mineral water, sparkling water, regular water,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.41,0:13:06.85,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,apple juice, orange juice, pineapple juice...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:09.10,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, you getting all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.44,0:13:12.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh? What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.94,0:13:15.27,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I asked if you wanted something to drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:17.86,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Why don't you get a nap in \N while you're at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:19.74,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You look beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.74,0:13:21.99,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'll keep an eye on the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.99,0:13:24.28,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:29.66,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,My shoulders feel stiff all of a sudden, \N and my back hurts. {sounds like someone we know}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:31.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,There we go...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:34.79,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'd really like something warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.79,0:13:36.34,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Something easy on the stomach. {OLD: Something that won't upset my stomach.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.34,0:13:39.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I told you, all we got is cold drinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:42.47,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Do you {\i1}ever{\i0} listen \N to what people tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:45.10,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'll just have a banana, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.22,0:13:51.06,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Man, gardens like these take my breath away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:52.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,They're so calming...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.94,0:13:55.90,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,So beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:14:03.49,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'd love nothing more than to reminisce about \N laying under the sun in the garden while I was a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:08.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, cut that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.87,0:14:12.66,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Licking your fingers before you \N turn the page is nasty! {Dat's nasty! -Shigechi}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.66,0:14:15.50,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh? Did I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:18.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Me? As if!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.80,0:14:29.47,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, you got something \N dangling out of your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.47,0:14:32.31,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}that's{\i0} nasty. \N What the hell is that? {Now DAT'S nasty! -Shigechi}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.31,0:14:33.35,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:37.56,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,A tooth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:41.07,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,For some reason, \N I can't eat the banana...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.74,0:14:46.57,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's all dried up... \N And really hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:51.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Oh, come on... \N You're just pulling my leg, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:57.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Man, you really got me... \N Thought that was a tooth for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:01.30,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wasn't very funny though, \N and I'm still kinda grossed out...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.30,0:15:03.63,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What's really hanging from your mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:09.22,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh? You ask me something again, Mista?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:12.98,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You'll have to speak up, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.98,0:15:16.19,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I didn't quite catch that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:21.28,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Like I said, this banana is falling apart...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:25.03,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-I can't eat it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.03,0:15:29.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-It's all dried up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.58,0:15:32.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,A-All the fruit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.58,0:15:34.91,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell happened to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.12,0:15:38.25,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}Didn't you hear me? Okay, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.87,0:15:38.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,There's something wrong with your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:40.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,N-Narancia, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.58,0:15:41.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'll speak louder for you this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.63,0:15:47.18,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You paying attention now?! \N I can't eat this banana!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.18,0:15:51.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Look! It just crumbles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.64,0:15:53.77,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's old and rotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.77,0:15:54.60,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:56.85,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I know! \N It's a Stand attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.85,0:16:00.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Th-There must be an enemy on the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.86,0:16:04.53,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh? What? \N What's this white stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.53,0:16:07.74,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It came from my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.74,0:16:11.16,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.16,0:16:12.66,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.16,0:16:16.21,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Did something... happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:21.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Th-They've all aged!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:29.72,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Mama... Wake up... Wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.09,0:16:32.76,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Mama... Mama...{You know, this might actually be the most disturbing scene in this show yet. -TLC}{Yeah, this is one of the few fights in Jojo where a bunch of inoccent people are attacked by a Stand, which you don't see too often. Most of the time when it does happen it's implied, but here's it's really explicit and disturbing. -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.81,0:16:38.10,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:46.11,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-Who the hell... i-is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.11,0:16:49.61,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What? Impossible... It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:52.07,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:55.62,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the fuck is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:57.83,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,A-A Stand that makes people age?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.83,0:17:02.00,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Did they figure out we're inside the tortoise?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:03.38,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Calm down, Mista.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.38,0:17:08.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If they knew we were inside the tortoise, \N they would have attacked us directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:13.64,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,And seeing as that's not the case, \N they have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:18.98,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The enemy probably only knows \N we're somewhere on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.98,0:17:23.94,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,In order to find Trish, \N they're attacking everyone on board indiscriminately!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:30.65,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,D-Does that mean everyone on board \N is being affected by this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:32.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.16,0:17:35.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They're desperate. \N I'm sure they'll try anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:37.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...without even a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.54,0:17:40.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This leaves us two choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:43.54,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,One: Take Trish and\N get off the train, somehow. {For BDs: What about "One: Take..." and "Or two: We..." for this line and the next? -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.54,0:17:48.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Or two: We find the enemy, even though\N we don't know their range, and eliminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:50.38,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're doing the second one, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:53.89,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If we wanna take her and run, \N we'd have to stop the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:56.01,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.39,0:17:59.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Assassination is one option we know will stop them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.77,0:18:03.10,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Assassinating them with my {Six Bullets of a Sexy Gun}{You mean Zipper Man of a Bruno? -G}{You mean a Golden Wind of Gold Experience? -T}{You mean Li'l Bomber of an Aeroplanesmith? -G v2.0}Sex Pistols!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:05.65,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You're absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.65,0:18:07.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But we don't have any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.73,0:18:10.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're aging at a rapid rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.36,0:18:12.95,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,B-Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:14.57,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,M-My hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.04,0:18:21.91,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Th-They're crumbling!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.54,0:18:24.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,They're falling apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:29.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You're right, Buccellati. \N We really don't have any time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:32.51,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Mista...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.13,0:18:35.89,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You can't go... just yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.89,0:18:38.64,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What are you saying, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.64,0:18:41.89,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm warning you... you can't go just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:44.02,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We don't have time to mess around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.02,0:18:44.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.69,0:18:46.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hear him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.27,0:18:48.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:54.40,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Why are we all aging at a \N different rate than Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:59.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista's and my symptoms are comparatively light...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.45,0:19:01.29,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish's even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:02.41,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.41,0:19:06.12,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're just aging at different rates is all! \N I'm going!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.12,0:19:11.59,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No... If they're attacking \N everyone indiscriminately with age...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.59,0:19:15.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,They could end up killing her as well, \N even though she's their target.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.72,0:19:19.35,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,There must be a condition \N determining the rate at which we're aging. {Edited for length -- if you can shrink this further, go for it. -QC A}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.06,0:19:21.89,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I have a hypothesis...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.39,0:19:28.27,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I believe the enemy is differentiating between men and women \N by the difference in their body temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.94,0:19:37.70,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I once read that women have more fat in their bodies, \N making them less susceptible to fluctuations in temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.70,0:19:43.16,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Supposedly women also age better \N and live longer than men.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:46.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's a bit warm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.37,0:19:52.38,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The enemy is differentiating the rate at which we're aging \N based on slight differences in body temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.38,0:19:56.17,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,All that matters is that \N the men age faster than the women.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.17,0:20:02.06,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That makes a lot of sense, \N but then why are you and I not aging the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.06,0:20:03.72,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You callin' me a girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.72,0:20:05.18,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Difference in body temperature...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.14,0:20:10.52,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, \N our bodies were slightly cooler...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:12.61,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...since we all drank cold drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.02,0:20:14.94,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Narancia had nothing to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:22.12,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Th-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.12,0:20:24.49,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno, it's exactly like you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.49,0:20:28.58,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're aging slower because \N our bodies are slightly cooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.42,0:20:32.88,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We gotta cool everyone down! \N {We'll use}Cool 'em using ice! {Edited for accuracy -QC A}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.88,0:20:34.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wait, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.25,0:20:36.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll have to take that ice with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.47,0:20:40.26,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I-Is this all we got? {Trish has like 10 ice cubes in her water glass but OK SURE ARAKI -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.26,0:20:43.68,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,None of this changes the fact that \N we need to eliminate the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:47.73,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista, you're going to \N take that ice and defeat them...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.73,0:20:52.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Before the ice melts \N and you lose your Stand power!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.32,0:21:01.32,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Just the driver... \N Doesn't look like anyone else is in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.54,0:21:08.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's so muggy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:12.33,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,This Stand really is attacking\N anyone and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:15.71,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I wonder if the tortoise is aging, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:18.63,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Although I've heard tortoises can \N pretty much live forever. {DEAR EDITOR JOSH-SAN: Remember the discussion we had about how "ten thousand" is sometimes used figuratively in Asian countries to just refer to a very, very large number and how we concluded that in this context that's probably the intent and therefore we should just have him say that he's heard they're srsly long-lived. -TLC OF THE TWENTIETH OF JANUARY 2020}{How about "[...] live fucking forever"? Maybe don't need the profanity, maybe do need a word like "practically" or a phrase like "more or less". -QC A}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.63,0:21:20.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Guess it'll outlive us...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.97,0:21:22.43,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Aww, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.76,0:21:26.89,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,What's Bro thinking? \N This is really dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.81,0:21:37.48,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,What's he gonna do if I get old, too? Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.48,0:21:39.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The air conditioner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.03,0:21:45.66,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If I cool down the driver's compartment, it should \N cool the inside of the tortoise too and slow down their aging! {anime logic 101}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:48.37,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,Got something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.00,0:21:51.46,Main,Pesci,0,0,0,,A little fishy took the bait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:56.25,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell is this hook-like thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.17,0:22:00.42,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,A d-different Stand than the one that's aging us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:03.39,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,There's another one? \N Two of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.72,0:22:05.55,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,There's two bad guys?!{OLD: There are two enemies?!}{Been thinkin' we could use a word other than "enemy" for 敵. If it doesn't work for Mista, switch back. Do consider other characters though. -QC A}
